# Theme Implementation Plan (Light / Dark Mode)

We will implement a seamless, flicker-free Light/Dark mode theme system for the entire application.

## Core Technologies & Dependencies
1. **`next-themes`**: The foundational library for React/Next.js theme switching.
   - **Why?** It automatically handles system preferences, saves the user's choice to `localStorage`, and injects a script into the `<head>` of the HTML to prevent **FOUC** (Flash of Unstyled Content) — so your page doesn't flash blindingly white before turning dark when the user visits.
2. **CSS Variables (Custom Properties)**: We will use native CSS variables (e.g., `var(--bg)`, `var(--text)`) to handle color changes dynamically without needing to write a massive amount of Javascript color calculations.
3. **`lucide-react`**: For the Sun / Moon toggle icon component (already installed).

