## Proposed Changes

### 1. Update Dependencies
- Run `npm install next-themes` to install the theme manager.

### 2. Configure Global CSS (`src/app/globals.css`)
#### [MODIFY] `globals.css`
- Restructure `:root {}` to serve as the default **Light Mode** palette (since the UI right now relies on white).
- Add a `.dark {}` class block to define the **Dark Mode** palette (reusing the cool dark colors currently trapped inside `:root`).
- Define specific variables for absolute control over text: `--bg-card`, `--border`, `--text-primary` (màu chữ chính), `--text-muted` (màu chữ xám phụ), và các biến màu hệ thống cho thẻ Tag/Nhãn (`--tag-green-bg`, `--tag-green-text`, `--tag-blue-bg`, v.v) để khi qua Dark Mode nó tự cân bằng Contrast (độ tương phản) mà không bị "mù" chữ.

### 3. Create Theme Provider (`src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx`)
#### [NEW] `ThemeProvider.tsx`
- Build a generic wrapper invoking `<ThemeProvider attribute="class" defaultTheme="system" enableSystem />` from `next-themes`.

### 4. Inject Provider into Root Layout (`src/app/layout.tsx`)
#### [MODIFY] `layout.tsx`
- Wrap `{children}` with the new `<ThemeProvider>`.

### 5. Build Theme Toggle Component (`src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx`)
#### [NEW] `ThemeToggle.tsx`
- Create a beautiful floating or TopNav button that reads the current theme from `useTheme()` and toggles between "light" and "dark". 
- Animate the Sun and Moon icons swapping using `framer-motion`.

### 6. Refactor Hardcoded Pages
#### [MODIFY] `src/app/(app)/daily/page.tsx`
#### [MODIFY] `src/app/(app)/daily/[day]/page.tsx`
